snippet.textDisplay: Bro 2 things bother me deeply. First is that he's no longer here with us. Second is that Mac was musically ahead of his time, he had to grow to get to this point, but if you take artist he became and he made his debut as this person he'd be highly received. Mac is one of the only rappers that's actually an ARTIST, in a world where everyone is getting more personal and talking mental health ect, mac has been hitting these topics for many years and it's why his fanbase is so diehard because we feel we know him personally. I think people get so caught up on young Mac that they don't respect this version of him enough to give him a listen. Divine Feminine was one his best works that gets looked over because no one wanted to hear a love album, it was unprecedented for a rapper to do stuff like that meanwhile it was excellent.

I lost my grandmother less than a year ago.
Spent over half my life in her house.
She did so much for me. Saw me to adulthood.


That first verse made me go look at her picture again and it makes today feel bittersweet.

I hope y'all are having a good day. And if you aren't, I hope it turns around.
Life gets weird. Life gets hard. Life gets stressful.
But you're here, kicking it, and listening to something beautiful.
Sometimes being alive is the best thing you've got, and that's okay.
You'll be okay.

Cheers.

snippet.textDisplay: Mac RIP brotha, you were a lyrical savant. As I've been told you were a wonderful&wholesome human being. I hoped to one day to collab with him (music is my passion, therapy&soul, I want to do the same for others). I cried the day he died, felt like I lost a brother, a part of me. U are still truly missed, which shows his greatness! God Bless to his family&friends. Gone but never forgotten! He was respected amongst many MCs&OGs in the rap game! That's how good he was! #MUSICAL LEGEND #RIP MOST DOPE, MR.SNAPBACK, THUMPS UP FOREVER!😥
